# project1.py

import pandas as pd
import csv
from collections import defaultdict

df = pd.read_csv("/Users/john/Downloads/population.csv")
print(df.head())

s = df["Value"]
mean_p = s.mean()
median_p = s.median()
mode_p = s.mode().iloc[0]

print("\n[Pandas results]")
print("Mean:", mean_p)
print("Median:", median_p)
print("Mode:", mode_p)

values = []
with open("/Users/john/Downloads/population.csv", newline="", encoding="utf-8") as f:
    reader = csv.DictReader(f)
    for row in reader:
        try:
            values.append(float(row["Value"]))
        except ValueError:
            continue

mean_std = sum(values) / len(values)
sorted_vals = sorted(values)
n = len(sorted_vals)
median_std = sorted_vals[n // 2] if n % 2 == 1 else (sorted_vals[n // 2 - 1] + sorted_vals[n // 2]) / 2
freq = {}
for v in sorted_vals:
    freq[v] = freq.get(v, 0) + 1
mode_std = max(freq, key=freq.get)

print("\n[Standard library results]")
print("Mean:", mean_std)
print("Median:", median_std)
print("Mode:", mode_std)

CSV_PATH = "/Users/john/Downloads/population.csv"
COUNTRY = "China"  # you can change this to "India" or "United States"

population_by_year = defaultdict(float)
with open(CSV_PATH, newline="", encoding="utf-8") as f:
    reader = csv.DictReader(f)
    for row in reader:
        if row["Country Name"] == COUNTRY:
            try:
                year = int(row["Year"])
                val = float(row["Value"])
                population_by_year[year] = val
            except ValueError:
                continue

years = sorted(population_by_year.keys())
max_val = max(population_by_year.values())
scale = 50 / max_val

print(f"\n[{COUNTRY} Population Over Time]")
for y in years:
    bar = "" * int(population_by_year[y] * scale)
    print(f"{y}: {bar} ({int(population_by_year[y])})")
